# Commit messages

- **Do not** name or reference Cursor, Claude, Copilot, Codex, ChatGPT, or other editor/assistant products in commit subjects or bodies. The changelog should read like maintainers wrote it, not like a tool signature.
- If you need attribution (nudge, pairing), use neutral wording (e.g. “refactor transcripts after review”) without product names.

## Examples

```text
❌ BAD: fix(api): websocket proxy — Cursor agent
❌ BAD: chore: typo (generated by Claude)

✅ GOOD: fix(api): websocket proxy reconnect
✅ GOOD: chore: fix typo in error copy
```

- Keep using [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) and the repo’s preference for concise subjects and substantive bodies only when necessary.
